{"author":{"id":"729f4229091d502775e0e5c4bfc138609955b348584d955f4229a3d76892d2a9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1506088766,"nonce":"rwQx4WkcNiMrPeRgFY3v6CmhzEQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNTk4MjQxNjQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1484","origin":"github"},"title":"DESeq2 normalized counts have bad column labels","message":"Someone in our local training course just noticed that the column labels in the normalized counts files have group labels, rather than sample labels. So you end up with labels like: `1: group 1`, `2: group 1`, `3: group 2`, etc. Given that people have a hard time tracking the exact order of samples within each group when the labels are removed, this should probably be changed. The relevant code [is here](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/deseq2/deseq2.R#L301). My preference would be to use the display name from the history item (possibly prepended with a number, as is currently done by the code to ensure things are unique).","files":null}]}